{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab6b1bb4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9321"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9321"},"text":"§ 9321.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Mandatory retirement: Superintendent of the United States Air Force Academy; waiver authority","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab6b1bb5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9321/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Mandatory Retirement","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Upon the termination of the detail of an officer to the position of Superintendent of the United States Air Force Academy, the Secretary of the Air Force shall retire the officer under any provision of this chapter under which the officer is eligible to retire.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab6b1bb6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9321/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Waiver Authority","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of Defense may waive the requirement in subsection (a) for good cause. In each case in which such a waiver is granted for an officer, the Secretary shall submit to the Committees on Armed Services of the Senate and the House of Representatives a written notification of the waiver, with a statement of the reasons supporting the decision that the officer not retire, and a written notification of the intent of the President to nominate the officer for reassignment. In the event a waiver under this subsection is granted, the subsequent nomination and appointment of such officer having served as Superintendent of the Academy to a further assignment in lieu of retirement shall be subject to the advice and consent of the Senate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab6b1bb7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/65/dA/tV/s532/a/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–65, div. A, title V, § 532(a)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/603"},"text":"113 Stat. 603","children":[],"tail":", § 8921; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/dA/tV/s541/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, div. A, title V, § 541(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", (c)(3)(A), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1902"},"text":"118 Stat. 1902","children":[],"tail":", 1904; renumbered § 9321, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s806/b/13"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 806(b)(13)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1833"},"text":"132 Stat. 1833","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/dA/tV/s509/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, div. A, title V, § 509(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/2560"},"text":"136 Stat. 2560","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab6b1bb8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab6b1bb9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab6b1bba-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263","children":[],"tail":" inserted at end “In the event a waiver under this subsection is granted, the subsequent nomination and appointment of such officer having served as Superintendent of the Academy to a further assignment in lieu of retirement shall be subject to the advice and consent of the Senate.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s8921"},"text":"section 8921 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375","children":[],"tail":" inserted “; waiver authority” after “Academy” in section catchline, designated existing provisions as subsec. (a), inserted heading, and added subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idab6b1bbb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab6b1bbc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2018 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-02-01"},"text":"Feb. 1, 2019","children":[],"tail":", with provision for the coordination of amendments and special rule for certain redesignations, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s800"},"text":"section 800 of Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3001"},"text":"section 3001 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idab6b1bbd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Application of Section to Superintendents Serving on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-05"},"text":"October 5, 1999","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section not applicable to an officer serving on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1999","children":[],"tail":", in the position of Superintendent of the United States Military Academy, Naval Academy, or Air Force Academy for so long as that officer continues on and after that date to serve in that position without a break in service, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/65/s532/a/5"},"text":"section 532(a)(5) of Pub. L. 106–65","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3921"},"text":"section 3921 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
